{"type":"assistant","message":{"content":[{"id":"toolu_vrtx_01GXnQz4kUa6gHyEo2bjCnEz","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/src/services/output-history-service.prizm","content":"MODULE: src/services/output-history-service\nFILES: output-history-service.js\nRESPONSIBILITY: In-memory ring buffer storing per-session AI CLI command output history for /output command retrieval\nKEY_FILES:\n- output-history-service.js: factory function, ~80 lines. No I/O, no external deps.\nDEPENDENCIES:\n- uses: none (no external dependencies)\n- imported-by: src/bot/commands/handlers/output.js (singleton instance)\n- imported-by: src/bot/telegram.js (via output.js re-export)\nTRAPS:\n- Ring buffer implemented with Array.push() + Array.shift() — not a true circular buffer. Performance is O(n) for eviction; acceptable for maxEntries <= 10.\n- outputHistoryService singleton is created inside output.js — telegram.js imports and uses this singleton. Tests must inject a mock via handlerCtx.outputHistoryService or they will mutate the shared singleton.\n- Session key format is telegram:{chatId} — must match the key used in telegram.js addOutput() call. If session key format changes in F-018, this must be updated.\n- getHistory() returns a slice of the internal array — returned objects are the same references. Callers must not mutate entries.\n- getHistory(sessionKey, 0) returns [] — count=0 is treated as \"no entries requested\".\nCHANGELOG:\n- 2026-03-22 | add: initial module for F-020 output history ring buffer\nUPDATED: 2026-03-22\n"},"name":"Write","type":"tool_use"}],"id":"req_vrtx_011CZJDqnjSYnjJZKd3tZrEM","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":181,"output_tokens":18,"cache_read_input_tokens":101092},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01AxNdFx22AqEXAnNaTghU15","session_id":"ac44fc5c-0407-4bd5-95fd-57d4b24826fc","uuid":"5f013e53-7954-4507-a0d1-