{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01AxETVdNWgPNtR4UW8f4JPK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Plan: F-020 — Enhanced Terminal Output Streaming\n     2→\n     3→## Architecture\n     4→\n     5→### Components\n     6→\n     7→1. **`src/utils/ansi-adapter.js`** (new)\n     8→   - Strip ANSI escape codes from raw terminal output\n     9→   - Convert basic ANSI colors to emoji markers (optional enhancement)\n    10→   - Collapse carriage-return (`\\r`) progress lines — keep only the last complete state per line group\n    11→\n    12→2. **`src/utils/output-segmenter.js`** (new)\n    13→   - Smart segmentation replacing hard-boundary `splitMessage()` for AI CLI output\n    14→   - Split at logical boundaries: code block fences (```), blank lines between paragraphs\n    15→   - Respect Telegram 4096-char limit (use 3800 as safe limit)\n    16→   - Never split inside a code block\n    17→\n    18→3. **`src/services/output-history-service.js`** (new)\n    19→   - In-memory ring buffer per session — stores last N command outputs (default: 10)\n    20→   - Each entry: `{ prompt: string, output: string, timestamp: number, index: number }`\n    21→   - API: `addOutput(sessionKey, prompt, output)`, `getHistory(sessionKey, count)`, `clearHistory(sessionKey)`\n    22→\n    23→4. **`src/bot/commands/handlers/output.js`** (new)\n    24→   - `/output [N]` command — show last N command outputs (default: 5, max: 20)\n    25→   - Format: numbered list with prompt + truncated output preview + timestamp\n    26→   - Uses `outputHistoryService` to retrieve entries\n    27→\n    28→5. **`src/bot/telegram.js`** (modify)\n    29→   - Import and register `/output` command\n    30→   - Integrate `ansiAdapter.processChunk()` in the `onChunk` hook (strip ANSI before pushing to streamPublisher)\n    31→   - Replace `splitMessage()` call in streaming path with `outputSegmenter.segmentOutput()`\n    32→   - After each AI CLI reply, call `outputHistoryService.addOutput()` to record the output\n    33→\n    34→### Data Flow\n    35→\n    36→```\n    37→AI CLI stdout → onChunk(rawText)\n    38→                → ansiAdapter.processChunk(rawText)  # strip ANSI, collapse \\r lines\n    39→                → streamPublisher.push(cleanText)     # stream to Telegram\n    40→\n    41→AI CLI done → routerResult.reply (full output)\n    42→            → ansiAdapter.stripAll(reply)            # clean full output for history\n    43→            → outputHistoryService.addOutput(sessionKey, userMessage, cleanOutput)\n    44→            → outputSegmenter.segmentOutput(cleanText)  # for final display\n    45→            → streamPublisher.setFinalText(segmentedText)\n    46→```\n    47→\n    48→### Interface Contracts\n    49→\n    50→```js\n    51→// src/utils/ansi-adapter.js\n    52→export function stripAnsi(text: string): string          // Remove all ANSI escape codes\n    53→export function collapseCarriageReturns(text: string): string  // Collapse \\r progress lines\n    54→export function processChunk(chunk: string): string       // stripAnsi + partial \\r handling\n    55→\n    56→// src/utils/output-segmenter.js\n    57→export function segmentOutput(text: string, maxChunkSize?: number): string[]  // Smart split\n    58→// Returns array of segments respecting code blocks and paragraphs\n    59→\n    60→// src/services/output-history-service.js\n    61→export function createOutputHistoryService(maxEntries?: number): OutputHistoryService\n    62→export interface OutputHistoryService {\n    63→  addOutput(sessionKey: string, prompt: string, output: string): void\n    64→  getHistory(sessionKey: string, count: number): OutputEntry[]\n    65→  clearHistory(sessionKey: string): void\n    66→}\n    67→\n    68→// src/bot/commands/handlers/output.js\n    69→export const outputMeta: CommandMeta\n    70→export async function handleOutput(handlerCtx: HandlerContext): Promise<void>\n    71→```\n    72→\n    73→## Files to Create\n    74→- `src/utils/ansi-adapter.js`\n    75→- `src/utils/output-segmenter.js`\n    76→- `src/services/output-history-service.js`\n    77→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/output.js`\n    78→- `tests/utils/ansi-adapter.test.js`\n    79→- `tests/utils/output-segmenter.test.js`\n    80→- `tests/services/output-history-service.test.js`\n    81→- `tests/bot/commands/output.test.js`\n    82→\n    83→## Files to Modify\n    84→- `src/bot/telegram.js` — register /output command, integrate ANSI adapter, smart segmentation, output history recording\n    85→\n    86→## Testing Approach\n    87→- Unit tests: ansi-adapter, output-segmenter, output-history-service (isolated, no external deps)\n    88→- Unit test: /output handler (mock outputHistoryService)\n    89→- Integration: telegram.js text handler processes ANSI-free chunks (mock executeAiCli with ANSI output)\n    90→\n    91→---\n    92→\n    93→## Tasks\n    94→\n    95→- [x] T1: Create `src/utils/ansi-adapter.js` with `stripAnsi`, `collapseCarriageReturns`, `processChunk`\n    96→- [x] T2: Write tests for `ansi-adapter.js` in `tests/utils/ansi-adapter.test.js`\n    97→- [x] T3: Create `src/utils/output-segmenter.js` with `segmentOutput`\n    98→- [x] T4: Write tests for `output-segmenter.js` in `tests/utils/output-segmenter.test.js`\n    99→- [x] T5: Create `src/services/output-history-service.js` with `createOutputHistoryService`\n   100→- [x] T6: Write tests for `output-history-service.js` in `tests/services/output-history-service.test.js`\n   101→- [x] T7: Create `/output` command handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/output.js`\n   102→- [x] T8: Write tests for `/output` handler in `tests/bot/commands/output.test.js`\n   103→- [x] T9: Modify `src/bot/telegram.js` — integrate ANSI adapter in `onChunk`, smart segmentation in final display, output history recording, register `/output` command\n   104→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD