{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_018ui2JaLFAdK8jTBEzEzMKD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"text":"---\n\n## prizmkit-code-review — F-020: Enhanced Terminal Output Streaming\n\n### Review Summary\n\n**Mode:** Feature review\n**Baseline:** `spec.md` acceptance criteria + `plan.md` interface contracts\n**Implementation Log:** Read and referenced throughout\n**Files Reviewed:** `src/utils/ansi-adapter.js`, `src/utils/output-segmenter.js`, `src/services/output-history-service.js`, `src/bot/commands/handlers/output.js`, `src/bot/telegram.js` (integration sections)\n\n---\n\n### Spec Compliance\n\nAll six acceptance criteria are satisfied:\n\n- **AC1** — ANSI stripping: `ansiProcessChunk(data.text)` wraps every `onAssistantChunk` before pushing to `streamPublisher` (`telegram.js:1017`). Coverage: full CSI/OSC/simple-ESC via `ANSI_REGEX`.\n- **AC2** — Carriage-return collapsing: `collapseCarriageReturns` inside `processChunk` splits on `\\n`, then collapses `\\r` segments within each line (`ansi-adapter.js:50-70`). Handles `\\r\\n` mixed input correctly.\n- **AC3** — Logical segmentation: `segmentOutput(fullText)` replaces `splitMessage` in the `render()` closure (`telegram.js:412`). Splits at paragraph boundaries first, then single newlines, then spaces; never splits inside a `\\`\\`\\`` fence pair.\n- **AC4** — /output history: `handleOutput` backed by `createOutputHistoryService` (ring buffer, default 10 per session). Command defaults 5 entries, caps at 20. Session key correctly prefixed as `telegram:{chatId}`.\n- **AC5** — Streaming latency: `STREAM_MIN_CHARS = 220` and `STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS = 1200` are preserved unchanged. No additional latency introduced.\n- **AC6** — Mobile readability: ANSI stripping produces clean text; logical segmentation avoids mid-code-block cuts.\n\n---\n\n### Findings\n\n| ID | Severity | Dimension | Location | Summary |\n|----|----------|-----------|----------|---------|\n| F1 | LOW | Plan Adherence | `telegram.js:1047` | Plan data flow specifies `ansiAdapter.stripAll(reply)` before `addOutput`, but implementation stores raw `routerResult.reply`. Dev's Decision 7 explicitly documents this as intentional — the TRAP in context-snapshot.md says \"output history must track FULL output (pre-split)\". No functional defect. |\n| F2 | LOW | Plan Adherence | `telegram.js:355-362` | `replyLargeText()` (zero-output fallback path at line 1041) still uses `splitMessage()`. Edge-case path only. The Implementation Log confirms the cross-channel push path was intentionally excluded from scope; this fallback is similarly low-risk but inconsistent. |\n| F3 | LOW | Consistency | `plan.md:81` | Plan lists test file as `tests/bot/commands/output.test.js`; actual file is at `tests/bot/commands/handlers/output.test.js`. No functional impact — test runs and passes. |\n| F4 | LOW | Consistency | `src/services/index.js` | `createOutputHistoryService` is not exported from `src/services/index.js`. root.prizm RULE states \"Services are registered in src/services/index.js.\" Currently no external consumers beyond the singleton in `output.js`, so no breakage. Consider adding for pattern consistency. |\n\n**No CRITICAL or HIGH findings.**\n\n---\n\n### Test Results\n\nCommand: `node --test tests/utils/ansi-adapter.test.js tests/utils/output-segmenter.test.js tests/services/output-history-service.test.js tests/bot/commands/handlers/output.test.js`\n\n```\nTests: 65 | Pass: 65 | Fail: 0 | Skipped: 0 | Duration: 86ms\n```\n\nAll 65 F-020-specific tests pass across four test files.\n\n---\n\n### Verdict: PASS\n\nNo CRITICAL or HIGH findings. All acceptance criteria are implemented. All 65 F-020 tests pass. Four LOW-severity items are recorded in `## Review Notes` in `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/020-enhanced-terminal-output-streaming/context-snapshot.md` for optional follow-up.\n\n**COMPLETION_SIGNAL: PASS**","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a235249f