uter (messageRouter lacks onHeartbeat hook)\n- bot._f018 is an internal namespace — not a stable public API\n- onAssistantChunk wraps chunk with ansiProcessChunk() (F-020) before pushing to streamPublisher — raw ANSI bytes from stdout are never forwarded to Telegram\n- segmentOutput() replaces splitMessage() in render() inside createEditableStreamPublisher — ONLY in streaming path; cross-channel push (subscribeCrossChannel) still uses splitMessage()\n- STREAM_MIN_CHARS (220) and STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS (1200) are preserved unchanged — segmentation only changes where cuts happen, not how often\n- outputHistoryService singleton exported from output.js — telegram.js imports it; tests must inject mock via handlerCtx to avoid mutating shared singleton state\nUPDATED: 2026-03-22\n"},"name":"Write","type":"tool_use"}],"id":"req_vrtx_011CZJEqA4RfGCLvk2RUjax3","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":604,"output_tokens":1,"cache_read_input_tokens":84173},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac44fc5c-0407-4bd5-95fd-57d4b24826fc","uuid":"fe06a560-689b-4829-aca7-62d85b67612c"}
